            "answer_text": "It depends on what you like the most\u2026 Studying medicine, you\u2019ll be ready to \u201csee\u201d what is wrong, think about how you can treat and make it better again. Studying biomedical science, you\u2019ll learn how pathogens interact with the human body, what it can cause, what can kill or make it stronger and so on. You also study a hell lot about the human body itself, your systems and anatomy. I\u2019m not sure if it\u2019s right to say but maybe medicine is the big picture, what people see more often and what take credit for your health getting better. In another hand, biomedical science may not be all show off, but it\u2019s there working hard as hell to give you a better diagnosis and help with prevention (vaccine, treatment, and stuff). ",
